The C library is maintained separately. Fetch it from
https://github.com/GregorR/musl , branch 'microcosm'.

To build Microcosm:

0 (if necessary)) Adjust your paths (. use.sh)

1) Build the cross-compiler (cd cross ; ./buildcc.sh)

2) Build host components of libmicrocosm
    cd libmicrocosm
    ./configure --prefix=/opt/cross/x86_64-pc-microcosm --target=x86_64-pc-microcosm
    make libmicrocosm.so libmicrocosm.so.1
    cp libmicrocosm.so* /opt/cross/x86_64-pc-microcosm/x86_64-pc-microcosm/lib

3) Build the dynamic loader
    cd gelfload
    ./configure --prefix=/opt/microcosm
    make all install

4) Build the C library, musl (cd musl ; cp ../musl.config.mak config.mak ; make all install)

5) Build libmicrocosm
    cd libmicrocosm
    make all install

6) Symlink the C library and host wrapper into the dynamic loader's path
    mkdir -p /opt/microcosm/lib/microcosm
    ln -s /opt/cross/x86_64-pc-microcosm/x86_64-pc-microcosm/lib/lib{c,microcosm}.so* /opt/microcosm/lib/microcosm/

7) Run stuff
    x86_64-pc-microcosm-gcc my-favorite-c-program.c
    /opt/microcosm/bin/microcosm ./a.out
